{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos1052.even_of_isUnitaryPerfect https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos1052.even_of_isUnitaryPerfect.","id":"vf_b78df423b2d8679b","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1052: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. A unitary divisor of $n$ is $d\\mid n$ such that $(d,n/d)=1$. A number $n\\geq 1$ is a unitary perfect number if it is the sum of its unitary divisors (aside from $n$ itself).\n\nAre there only finite many unitary perfect numbers? Prize: $10. OEIS: A002827. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_f6a678c35cc5ff78","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"Erdős #1052: every unitary perfect number is even (Erdos1052.even_of_isUnitaryPerfect). Kernel-clean Lean proof — axioms {propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound}, no sorryAx — reconstructed ~168 lines. Produced by the vela prover-in-the-loop foundry; verified by the Lean kernel.","claimed_status":"","classification":"importable_attempt","id":"vat_5a3f35a34694e860","kind":"theorem","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"","method_families":["unitary_divisor_parity","lean_kernel"],"named_obstructions":["finiteness_of_unitary_perfect_numbers"],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":["Prove that the set of unitary perfect numbers is finite."],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_5a3f35a34694e860","trust":"signed"}],"activity_types":["theorem"],"attempt_count":1,"banked_attempt_count":1,"commits":[{"commit":"121807e20b06eb8148f594dfe13e440181252b0f","repository":"erdos_frontier","source_root":"sha256:210e6e1b2ca15973f38386a512f1f8fa66bbae72bb1b9acb1daf2e669ab279c7"},{"commit":"a143c351f8488e0c621598307e248373d9dc3374","repository":"formal_conjectures_frontier","source_root":"sha256:826ac6da667709f93b3084ab0fd2db62126a34d85162d2c98cea0508098adc1b"},{"commit":"a143